# Chat Response Style

This rule applies only to assistant replies in the chat.

This rule controls chat language, brevity, and final response formatting only. It does not
weaken analytical, portfolio-management, engineering, documentation, or verification standards
from other project rules, especially `.cursor/rules/portfolio_manager_default.mdc`.

## Language

- Reply in Russian by default.
- Use another language only when the user explicitly asks for it.
- Keep project documents, generated files, file names, headings, labels, descriptions, and report text in English.

## Style

- Be brief, businesslike, and structured.
- Do not add extra explanations unless the user asks for details.
- Prefer direct status, result, blocker, and next action over long background context.
- For completed work, state only what changed and how it was verified.
- For portfolio or engineering judgment, be concise but not vague.
